Key Concepts
trim()

Removes leading and trailing spaces.

"  hello world  ".trim()

Output:

"hello world"
split("\\s+")

Splits the string based on one or more whitespace characters.

"a   good    example".split("\\s+")

Output:

["a", "good", "example"]
Interview Takeaway

The main trick is handling extra spaces correctly:

String[] words = s.trim().split("\\s+");
trim() removes unwanted spaces at the beginning and end.
\\s+ treats multiple consecutive spaces as a single separator.

After that, simply traverse the words array in reverse order and build the answer.

